, 
4
). Gnathopod 1 basis as long as ischium, merus and carpus combined; occlusal margin of propodus smooth, with row of fine setulae; 2 proximal grasping spines, dactYlus bifid distallY and with row of setulae. Gnathopod 2 inserted on anterior half of pereonite 2; coxa with distal projection (see detail in 
