); basis about 2/3 length of pereonite 2, with tinY tubercles similar to those on pereonites; ischium rectangular; basis and ischium with distal projection laterallY; merus rounded; carpus short, triangular; propodus palm with proximal projection with large grasping spine, serrated area, medial projection, and 2 more projections distallY (
Fig. 4
); dactYlus smooth and elongate, with verY fine setulae onlY.
